6: Pathetic. To think, I let this happen...
20:
You're bleeding! Are you okay?!
What did this?! Monsters?!
24:
I'm fine. The scratches are nothing to 
worry about. They just nicked me.
26:
Just... just a little sore about how 
powerless this body is, how powerless 
I am. What good is this tiny body?
30: Well, it's very cute, for one.
35:
Cute?! CUTE?! What use is THAT?! 
I—
37:
*sigh* No, you're right.
I'm sorry for snapping at you.
Forget this. All of this.
43: Hm... The wind is picking up.
51:
The wind? What's gotten in to you all 
of a—
Wait! WAIT! WAIT AURORE! AUROREEE!
61:
It, it DOES, but...
D-don't you DARE let g-go!
65:
The stars look beautiful from here.
It's a shame they're so far away.
68:
It was always my dream to visit one, 
back when I was a hatchling. To fly up, 
and up, and up until I reached them.
75:
I know now that might not be possible. 
That IS awfully far to fly, even for 
birdfolk. I've given up on the idea.
78:
Fair enough. Not much sense to keep 
trying, is there? It's a nice dream, 
though.
82:
Right? It would have been nice to fly 
there myself, but the other options 
I have are much more promising!
84:
The winds may not have carried me to 
the stars, but they carried me to you. 
To real, live star-hoppers!
87:
I know your "worlds" aren't exactly the 
same as the canyon's stars, but 
they're a start.
89:
With the World Flipper and all of you at 
my side, visiting the stars doesn't feel 
like a dream anymore! Now it's my 
goal!
93: You sure do beat to your own drum...
101:
They're a sight to behold. 
I suppose this tiny body isn't all so 
bad.
103:
In my original body, I would have been 
too heavy to carry this high.
108:
Really? I'm glad. Thank YOU for taking 
me in, even after I accidentally 
attacked you in the canyon. You truly 
have a champion's heart!
112: Aurore? Can I ask you a favor?
114:
If you don't mind... it would be nice to 
stay like this for a bit.
118: Ahaha, of course! We've got all night!
